    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "## Show link oembed when adding a link to an edited message.\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user I want to see link previews any time a link is shared so that I have a consistent message experience.\r\n\r\nFeature: **Messages**\r\n\r\n#### Background:\r\n\r\n- GIVEN I have an account\r\n  - I open the app\r\n  - I am logged in\r\n  - I am on a chat screen\r\n\r\n#### Scenario: *Sending a message containing a link*\r\n\r\n- GIVEN I am composing a message\r\n- AND I have added a link to the message\r\n- AND I allow the application to make http calls\r\n- THEN I see an oembed for the added link in the message preview\r\n- WHEN I send the message\r\n- THEN I see the message in the chat\r\n- AND I see the link preview / oembed below the message.\r\n\r\n#### Scenario: *Receive a new message containing a link*\r\n\r\n- GIVEN I receive a message containing a link\r\n- THEN I see the message body, containing links\r\n- AND I see an oembed card for each link below the main message\r\n- WHEN I tap on the oembed card, the app opens the link in my default browser\r\n\r\n#### Scenario\r\n\r\nTODO add scenario where the user see oembed when receiving even if making http calls is disallowed (because we bundle oembed into the payload.)",
